# ── Environment contract ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The Cloudflare adapter feeds `vars` from wrangler.jsonc into import.meta.env
# at build time, and astro.config.mjs falls back to the same wrangler vars for
# Astro's `site` (sitemap/RSS/llms.txt URLs). So for deployed builds, set
# PUBLIC_* values in wrangler.jsonc `vars` — that is the single source of
# truth. Shell env vars (this file / CI env) still take precedence when set;
# if you set PUBLIC_SITE_URL in the shell, keep wrangler.jsonc in sync.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Public: canonical origin (e.g. https://lyrasecai.com). Preview builds should use the workers.dev URL.
PUBLIC_SITE_URL="http://localhost:4321"

# Public: X/Twitter profile URL. Leave unset to hide the link entirely.
# PUBLIC_X_URL="https://x.com/lyrasecai"

# Public: set to "true" only on the real production domain after founder go-live.
# NOTE: for deployed builds this is read from wrangler.jsonc `vars`, not this file.
PUBLIC_INDEXABLE="false"

# Public: PostHog project key. Leave unset to disable analytics entirely.
# PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY="phc_..."

# Public: PostHog host. Default is the EU endpoint.
PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST="https://eu.i.posthog.com"

# Secret: random 32+ character salt for ip_hash.
# In local dev wrangler reads secrets from `.dev.vars` (not `.env`). Copy `.dev.vars.example` and update it there.
# WAITLIST_IP_SALT=""
